The paper deals with sparse recovery and sketching, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT), data structures (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of metrics and norms also suggests the possibility of numerical analysis (cs.NA) being a relevant sub-category. Finally, the mention of clustering problems and streaming models points towards the area of algorithms and data structures (cs.SI).
